<kml>

<concept name=Be-Activated><system-documentation name=Be-Activated>

<superconcept name=Be-Accessible>

<definition>

   An <slot>object</slot> becomes activated.  This is a specific type
   of accessibility.

  An object is put in this state by <conceptref name=Activate>.

</definition>

<requiredslotlist>

   <slotdescription name=object>
      the thing that becomes activated
   </slotdescription>

</requiredslotlist>

<examplesentencelist>

   <examplesentence>
     <text>Sally turned on the computer.</text>
     <slotdescription name=object>the computer</slotdescription>
   </examplesentence>
   <comment> 
      "Turned on" here would be represented by an <conceptref name=Activate>
      action, where the activation of the computer would be a result.
   </comment>
   
   <examplesentence>
     <text>Jerome armed the motion sensor.</text>
     <slotdescription name=object>the motion sensor</slotdescription>
   </examplesentence>
   <comment>
      Activation is distinct from Operation.  The motion sensor can now be
      used; triggering the motion sensor would not be an activate, since
      it is already activated.
   </comment>

</examplesentencelist>

<neighborlist>

   <neighbor name=Be-Accessible>
      Be-Accessible is generally for accessible things not covered by
      more specific concepts.
   </neighbor>

   <neighbor name=Be-Open>
      Be-Open is specifically for a <conceptref name=Portal-Cover>, so that 
      it is removed from the  <conceptref name=Portal>.
   </neighbor>

</neighborlist>

</kml>


